From e2301d16315db200006c2fa2e75e8f2d330146e6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 14:20:52 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 4: per-workspace bot list
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Comments authored by users on a workspace's bot list now route to
Automation instead of Discussion. The list is per-workspace (keyed by
folder URI) and persisted under `krt.botList.v1`.

- `IKrtBotListService` exposes `getBots / addBot / removeBot / isBot`
  plus an `onDidChange(folderUri)` event so the active PR pane re-
  renders when the list changes.
- `KRT: Add Bot User…` builds its picker from the active PR's
  commenters (issue + review + automation actors) and falls back to
  free-form input. `KRT: Remove Bot User…` quick-picks from the
  workspace's existing entries.
- The activity classifier in `KrtPullRequestEditorPane` partitions
  `liveComments` into Discussion / bot piles per PR. Bot comments are
  merged into the Automation timeline by timestamp so the row order
  tracks chronology.
